author: Gerald F. Seib
title: Analysis: Hillary Clinton Shows Relentless Efficiency in First Democratic Debate - WSJ
text:
Hillary Clinton sometimes is criticized as being polarizing, or programmed, or humorless. But give her credit for this: She can be relentlessly efficient.
Within the first hour of the initial Democratic debate Tuesday night, she had labeled herself a progressive, but one who knows how to get results.
